attr><attrlabl Sync="TRUE">OPP_DISTRI</attrlabl><attalias Sync="TRUE">OPP_DISTRI</attalias><attrtype Sync="TRUE">String</attrtype><attwidth Sync="TRUE">254</attwidth><atprecis Sync="TRUE">0</atprecis><attscale Sync="TRUE">0</attscale><attrdef>OPP Districts in Ontario as defined within the Linear Highway Referencing System. (16 districts in total)</attrdef></attr><attr xmlns=""><attrlabl Sync="TRUE">COUNTY</attrlabl><attalias Sync="TRUE">COUNTY</attalias><attrtype Sync="TRUE">Double</attrtype><attwidth Sync="TRUE">10</attwidth><atprecis Sync="TRUE">10</atprecis><attscale Sync="TRUE">0</attscale><attrdef>County which the basepoint is located in.</attrdef><attrdefs>MMAH</attrdefs></attr><attr xmlns=""><attrlabl Sync="TRUE">HWY</attrlabl><attalias Sync="TRUE">HWY</attalias><attrtype Sync="TRUE">String</attrtype><attwidth Sync="TRUE">4</attwidth><atprecis Sync="TRUE">0</atprecis><attscale Sync="TRUE">0</attscale><attrdef>Highway number as defined within the Linear Highway Referencing System</attrdef><attrdefs>MTO</attrdefs></attr><attr xmlns=""><attrlabl Sync="TRUE">LHRS</attrlabl><attalias Sync="TRUE">LHRS</attalias><attrtype Sync="TRUE">Double</attrtype><attwidth Sync="TRUE">10</attwidth><atprecis Sync="TRUE">10</atprecis><attscale Sync="TRUE">0</attscale><attrdef>An LHRS Base Point number is a location referencing point along the Provincial Highway Network. LHRS Base Point numbers are known field identifiable locations along the network which are used to defined individual sections of a highway. The Base Point number consists of five digits. The numbers increment in an increasing fashion along the highway. As a highway numbers increase, the basepoint numbers also increase. Sorting on this field will result in an ordered set of LHRS Base Points by highway.</attrdef><attrdefs>MTO</attrdefs></attr><attr xmlns=""><attrlabl Sync="TRUE">LENGTH</attrlabl><attalias Sync="TRUE">LENGTH</attalias><attrtype Sync="TRUE">Double</attrtype><attwidth Sync="TRUE">19</attwidth><atprecis Sync="TRUE">18</atprecis><attscale Sync="TRUE">8</attscale><attrdef>The distance along the Highway from the any LHRS Base Point to the next higher number LHRS Base Point. These distances are driven distance lengths.</attrdef><attrdefs>MTO</attrdefs></attr><attr xmlns=""><attrlabl Sync="TRUE">OFFSET</attrlabl><attalias Sync="TRUE">OFFSET</attalias><attrtype Sync="TRUE">Double</attrtype><attwidth Sync="TRUE">10</attwidth><atprecis Sync="TRUE">10</atprecis><attscale Sync="TRUE">0</attscale><attrdef>The distance of an event located on the highway from the LHRS Base Point that defines the section of highway.</attrdef><attrdefs>MTO</attrdefs></attr><attr><attrlabl Sync="TRUE">DESCRIPTIO</attrlabl><attalias Sync="TRUE">DESCRIPTIO</attalias><attrtype Sync="TRUE">String</attrtype><attwidth Sync="TRUE">254</attwidth><atprecis Sync="TRUE">0</atprecis><attscale Sync="TRUE">0</attscale></attr><attr xmlns=""><attrlabl Sync="TRUE">ASSUMED</attrlabl><attalias Sync="TRUE">ASSUMED</attalias><attrtype Sync="TRUE">String</attrtype><attwidth Sync="TRUE">254</attwidth><atprecis Sync="TRUE">0</atprecis><attscale Sync="TRUE">0</attscale><attrdef>If a LHRS Base Point is located on a section of highway under the jurisdiction of MTO it is said to be “Assumed” (A). If a LHRS Base Point is located on a section of highway not under the jurisdiction of MTO it is said to be “Non-Assumed” (NA).</attrdef><attrdefs>MTO</attrdefs></attr><attr xmlns=""><attrlabl Sync="TRUE">DIRECTION</attrlabl><attalias Sync="TRUE">DIRECTION</attalias><attrtype Sync="TRUE">String</attrtype><attwidth Sync="TRUE">254</attwidth><atprecis Sync="TRUE">0</atprecis><attscale Sync="TRUE">0</attscale><attrdef>This field contains the cardinal direction of the highway section defined by the LHRS Base Point, in relation to the direction of highway measure direction.</attrdef><attrdefs>MTO</attrdefs></attr><attr><attrlabl Sync="TRUE">FROM_MEASU</attrlabl><attalias Sync="TRUE">FROM_MEASU</attalias><attrtype Sync="TRUE">Double</attrtype><attwidth Sync="TRUE">19</attwidth><atprecis Sync="TRUE">18</atprecis><attscale Sync="TRUE">8</attscale></attr><attr xmlns=""><attrlabl Sync="TRUE">TO_MEASURE</attrlabl><attalias Sync="TRUE">TO_MEASURE</attalias><attrtype Sync="TRUE">Double</attrtype><attwidth Sync="TRUE">19</attwidth><atprecis Sync="TRUE">18</atprecis><attscale Sync="TRUE">8</attscale><attrdef>The distance from the beginning of the highway of the end of the section of highway defined by the  Base Point</attrdef><attrdefs>MTO</attrdefs></attr><attr xmlns=""><attrlabl Sync="TRUE">LATITUDE</attrlabl><attalias Sync="TRUE">LATITUDE</attalias><attrtype Sync="TRUE">Double</attrtype><attwidth Sync="TRUE">19</attwidth><atprecis Sync="TRUE">18</atprecis><attscale Sync="TRUE">8</attscale><attrdef>The longitude value of the Base Point</attrdef><attrdefs>MTO</attrdefs></attr><attr xmlns=""><attrlabl Sync="TRUE">LONGITUDE</attrlabl><attalias Sync="TRUE">LONGITUDE</attalias><attrtype Sync="TRUE">Double</attrtype><attwidth Sync="TRUE">19</attwidth><atprecis Sync="TRUE">18</atprecis><attscale Sync="TRUE">8</attscale><attrdef>The latitude value of the Base Point</attrdef><attrdefs>MTO</attrdefs></attr></detailed></eainfo><mdDateSt Sync="TRUE">20160404</mdDateSt><Binary><Thumbnail><Data EsriPropertyType="PictureX">/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQEAAQABAAD/2wBDAAgGBgcGBQgHBwcJCQgKDBQNDAsLDBkSEw8UHRofHh0a
